fetchIssueById.title: sdfsdf
fetchIssueById.bodyHTML:
Descripription

There is a problem with the test for the telephone validator. They pass validators which do not check for proper spacing or dashing. (i. e. my validator will return true for 55 55-55-555-5).
This is the my code which passed the test, but really shouldn't have:

 let firstReg=new RegExp("^\-");
  if(firstReg.test(str)){return false;}
  let regEx= new RegExp("-","g");
  console.log(firstReg);
  let newStr=str.replace(regEx,"");
  let newRegEx= new RegExp(" ","g")
  newStr=newStr.replace( newRegEx,"");
  console.log(newStr);
  let regExArr=[/^\d\d\d\d\d\d\d\d\d\d$/, /^[(]\d\d\d[)]\d\d\d\d\d\d\d$/, /^1[(]\d\d\d[)]\d\d\d\d\d\d\d$/, /^1\d\d\d\d\d\d\d\d\d\d$/];
  for(let i=0; i<regExArr.length; i++){
    if(regExArr[i].test(newStr)){
      console.log(i);
      return regExArr[i].test(newStr);
    }```

githubIssues.title: No way to disable HMR (hot-module-reload)
githubIssues.body:
### Verify canary release

- [X] I verified that the issue exists in Next.js canary release

### Provide environment information

Hot-module-reload is extremely unreliable for me. It doesn't work maybe 10% of the time, and this causes serious problems when I expect it to work and it doesn't.

For me, at least in this specific project I'm working on (not in Next.js in general), any tool that is unreliable like this needs to get tossed. The fact that we cannot do this in Next.js is absurd.

Please reopen https://github.com/vercel/next.js/issues/1109
